le?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 499<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 7:29:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level Restriction explained!</span><hr size=1> Hmmph, I liked it better when they had people complaining... Most items that you can get when you are over 40 should have a recommended level of at least 30 or something so that people would actually follow what we did when we started, cloth, patchwork, leather, banded, bronze, plate, quest armor, then you're over 30 and can go for the good magical stuff... same with weapon, there are still plenty good weapons for those under 30 to be used which won't make a different in how you kill monsters (unless you are trying to power level yourself), I used a polish granite tomahawk until I was 25-30 or so and still had a blackened alloy bastard sword equipped at 40 and it did not cause me any problems so I really don't know where the big deal is/was with all the complaints. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usllackblader.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sllack Blader</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 11:38:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level Restriction explained!</span><hr size=1> I think FV will be the least impacted of any server, mainly due to the lack of twinks because of 1 char/account.<br><br>But on standard blue servers I always felt it was the god given right of someone to PL and/or twink an alt if they so desired. I mean, if you spend all that time to make a 60 char and you want to play something different, why not give the alt some of your hard earned loot and pp?<br><br>Anyways impact to FV = low, impact to EQ in general = high, IMHO. <p><center><a href="http://www.kanebayle.com"><img src="http://www.kanebayle.com/love2.gif"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 12:06:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level Restriction explained!</span><hr size=1> The problem is that irresponsible twinkage tends to impact the gameplay of others - rather negatively. The level 4 twink in planar gear monopolizing a whole camp designed for a group of level 12 characters is a bit unfair to that whole group of level 12s. Multiply this by scores of twinks, and suddenly you have almost a class-based distribution of hunting areas.<br><br>Twinks tend to take alot of the primo hunting - at least that was my experience back in the day on Cazic. It was one of several factors that led me to quit EQ - not jealousy (they are welcome to their stuff), but their attitude. The idea that because some guy has 'played to 60' or whatever, they are entitled to lord it over others on a perpetual basis is just arrogant. The newbie who is trying to play the game as intended is paying the same amount per month, and is just as entitled to an enjoyable game. The casual gamer is just as entitled to value for their dollar as a hardcore gamer.<br><br>Several of the other recent changes in EQ and alot of other online games have been to address these sorts of issues. The real profit for a gaming company comes from meeting the entertainment needs of a horde of casual gamers, rather than catering to a small group of highly-competitive players who can dedicate large amounts of time to the game.<br><br>No insult intended or implied to responsible twinkers, who play with respect towards others. All disdain aimed at selfish wankers.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Opinionated L'il Gnome <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umrgoodkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Goodkin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 12:25:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level Restriction explained!</span><hr size=1> What Gnome is opinionated? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>May Brell shine the light in your eyes ~ <BR> Goody <BR> Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1725.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1725.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign